nceOf[Class[T]], name)\n1245:     * static <code>forClass(java.lang.Class<T> classToMock)</code> method in Java class <code>org.mockito.Mockito</code>).\n1248:     * Using the Mockito API directly, you create a ArgumentCaptor with:\n1276:   * Companion object that facilitates the importing of <code>MockitoSugar</code> members as \n1277:   * an alternative to mixing it in. One use case is to import <code>MockitoSugar</code> members so you can use\n1281:  object MockitoSugar extends MockitoSugar\n1299:  package org.scalatestplus.mockito\n1301:  import org.mockito.Mockito.{mock => mockitoMock}\n1303:  import org.mockito.stubbing.Answer\n1304:  import org.mockito.ArgumentCaptor\n1305:  import org.mockito.MockSettings\n1308:   * Trait that provides some basic syntax sugar for <a href=\"http://mockito.org/\" target=\"_blank\">Mockito</a>.\n1311:   * Using the Mockito API directly, you create a mock with:\n1334:  trait MockitoSugar {\n1337:     * Invokes the <code>mock(classToMock: Class[T])</code> method on the <code>Mockito</code> companion object (<em>i.e.</em>, the\n1338:     * static <code>mock(java.lang.Class<T> classToMock)</code> method in Java class <code>org.mockito.Mockito</code>).\n1341:     * Using the Mockito API directly, you create a mock with:\n1357:      mockitoMock(classTag.runtimeClass.asInstanceOf[Class[T]])\n1361:     * Invokes the <code>mock(classToMock: Class[T], defaultAnswer: Answer[_])</code> method on the <code>Mockito</code> companion object (<em>i.e.</em>, the\n1362:     * static <code>mock(java.lang.Class<T> classToMock, org.mockito.stubbing.Answer defaultAnswer)</code> method in Java class <code>org.mockito.Mockito</code>).\n1365:     * Using the Mockito API directly, you create a mock with:\n1381:      mockitoMock(classTag.runtimeClass.asInstanceOf[Class[T]], defaultAnswer)\n1385:     * Invokes the <code>mock(classToMock: Class[T], mockSettings: MockSettings)</code> method on the <code>Mockito</code> companion object (<em>i.e.</em>, the\n13