in MockitoSugar are covered, and it seems there might be one left: the implicit conversion on captors. The current capture test does employ implicit conversion, so that aspect is covered. However, the companion object's import of members isn’t addressed yet. I definitely need to assess the coverage and add a test to the same file without altering the existing logic. It might help to define an object helper to clarify the imports instead of extending the trait directly. This could allow for a clearer test structure.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Reviewing companion imports**\\\\n\\\\nI’m considering if this test on companion object imports really counts as a retest of the class. It will create a mock and a stub, following the same flow as typing a mock. But since this focuses on demonstrating an alternative import feature, it might be acceptable. I just need to ensure that it clearly showcases how the companion object works, rather than duplicating what’s already been tested with mocks.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_nN5oICk5dHKqnQ6QRzfwin9q|fc_054c94571e071d260169fa73bbf1b4819cb6377e63ae3013c7\", \"name\": \"edit\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"tests/src/org.scalatestplus/mockito-5-12_3/3.2.19.0/src/test/scala/org_scalatestplus/mockito_5_12_3/Mockito_5_12_3Test.scala\", \"edits\": [{\"oldText\": \"  @Test\\n  def captureCreatesTypedArgumentCaptorsAndImplicitlyCapturesDuringVerification(): Unit =\\n    exerciseMockitoDynamicClassGeneration {\\n      val sink: AuditSinkForMockito_5_12_3Test = mock[AuditSinkForMockito_5_12_3Test]\\n      val firstEvent: AuditEventForMockito_5_12_3Test = AuditEventForMockito_5_12_3Test(\\\"created\\\", 1)\\n      val secondEvent: AuditEventForMockito_5_12_3Test = AuditEventForMockito_5_12_3Test(\\\"updated\\\", 2)\\n      val captor: ArgumentCaptor[AuditEventForMockito_5_12_3Test] = capture[AuditEventForMockito_5_12_3Test]\\n\\n      sink.publish(firstEvent)\\n      sink.publish(secondEven